[7.970086, "o", "The AI RMF definition of risk relates to the impact levels in FIPS 199 as follows: The AI RMF defines risk as \"the likelihood and potential impact that a threat will exploit vulnerabilities in an information system\" [1], which is consistent with the concept of impact value in FIPS 199, where the assessed worst-case potential impact is expressed as a value of low, moderate or high [2].\r\n\u001b[90m[request 501d2b869dc74701a54c110101e036b8]\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.970104, "o", "\u001b[90m[audit data/audit/audit-20260712.jsonl]\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n[1] ai-rmf §appendix-d (p.46)\r\n[2] ai-rmf §1.2.4 (p.12)\r\n\u001b[90m[planner 0.55s | retrieve 0.15s | synthesize 1.75s | critic 0.79s | guardrails_in 0.00s | guardrails_out 0.00s]\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m[ollama] 4592 in / 124 out / cost $0.0000\u001b[0m\r\n"]
